10/03/2010
WASHINGTON, United States -- Homeland Security Secretary Janet Napolitano announced on Tuesday (March 9th) that Greece has been added to the list of countries whose citizens do not need visas to travel to the United States.
She praised the readiness of Greek authorities to boost air transportation security.
Greek citizens will be eligible to travel visa-free within 30 days.
(AFP, ITAR-TASS, ANA-MPA - 09/03/10)
